{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-chapter-level-2-chapter-level-2-tsx","path":"/topics/retinal-detachment/diagnosis/diagnosis/","result":{"pageContext":{"chapter":{"id":"8f1c2235-30d5-59ca-b646-048edf6147eb","slug":"diagnosis","fullItemName":"Diagnosis","depth":2,"htmlHeader":"<!-- begin field e0dee44a-37c1-48cf-a790-2e2c20b214bc --><h2>When should I suspect retinal detachment?</h2><!-- end field e0dee44a-37c1-48cf-a790-2e2c20b214bc -->","summary":"","htmlStringContent":"<!-- begin item 7726dae1-c44a-4d94-b75f-3d9484b9a391 --><!-- begin field 2df53bd7-64a6-4f7e-8532-2f140bf67623 --><p><strong>Suspect a diagnosis of retinal detachment if the person has:</strong></p><ul><li>New onset of floaters.<ul><li>These describe the perception of mobile dots, lines, or haze of varying translucency caused by blood, pigment cells, and inflammatory debris entering the vitreous cavity casting shadows on the retina.</li></ul></li><li>New onset of flashes.<ul><li>These describe the perception of light often seen as recurrent, brief flashes, caused by traction on the retina as the vitreous pulls away.</li></ul></li><li>Sudden-onset painless and usually progressive visual field loss.<ul><li>This may be described as a dark curtain or shadow, which usually starts in the periphery and progresses towards the centre over hours, days, or weeks as the detachment extends.</li><li>If the macula detaches, central visual acuity may be severely reduced.</li></ul></li><li>A reduction in visual acuity, blurred or distorted vision, causing persistent and progressive visual loss.</li><li>Note: be aware that it may be more difficult to recognize retinal detachment in children, as they are less likely to report reduced vision or visual disturbance.<ul><li>Infants usually present with a white pupillary reflex (leukocoria) or squint (strabismus).</li></ul></li></ul><!-- end field 2df53bd7-64a6-4f7e-8532-2f140bf67623 --><!-- end item 7726dae1-c44a-4d94-b75f-3d9484b9a391 -->","topic":{"id":"9be2cb0d-8648-5694-a09c-292ca1ced19e","topicId":"e3f75bdf-a207-4239-9931-367d38a9b7d6","topicName":"Retinal detachment","slug":"retinal-detachment","lastRevised":"Last revised in August 2019","chapters":[{"id":"842ff08c-c002-50cd-bab2-348ba3e67be0","fullItemName":"Summary","slug":"summary","subChapters":[]},{"id":"98f29b98-1286-5c16-a606-4cd90cc70465","fullItemName":"Have I got the right topic?","slug":"have-i-got-the-right-topic","subChapters":[]},{"id":"873d5520-2d22-5b9d-bd04-6d9112dc82ee","fullItemName":"How up-to-date is this topic?","slug":"how-up-to-date-is-this-topic","subChapters":[{"id":"3b54abb3-d415-51e3-996b-1d6e3bcc3d3b","slug":"changes","fullItemName":"Changes"},{"id":"0aa87cea-a601-54db-9dcb-ec3117e7098a","slug":"update","fullItemName":"Update"}]},{"id":"dbe4b4fd-c326-5686-bd9a-71905fc13c76","fullItemName":"Goals and outcome measures","slug":"goals-outcome-measures","subChapters":[{"id":"9f38c5e9-5edd-56fa-a740-0d19004a69af","slug":"goals","fullItemName":"Goals"},{"id":"5960233a-64c2-5a35-95ea-6a44ae788808","slug":"outcome-measures","fullItemName":"Outcome measures"},{"id":"e506d9ce-54a0-57f2-b4d1-49bb28e3d283","slug":"audit-criteria","fullItemName":"Audit criteria"},{"id":"0ce8a869-7cf6-588c-b609-d5a90fa6adf0","slug":"qof-indicators","fullItemName":"QOF indicators"},{"id":"a1808dfe-2608-5274-a314-61a4054cb431","slug":"qipp-options-for-local-implementation","fullItemName":"QIPP - Options for local implementation"},{"id":"6148c790-0603-5594-9e2f-9d1a8bdaab45","slug":"nice-quality-standards","fullItemName":"NICE quality standards"}]},{"id":"17128c85-3baa-5f71-a71e-69028c5e8e6a","fullItemName":"Background information","slug":"background-information","subChapters":[{"id":"4d268a45-69b2-5f94-9f83-4e3bde2a12b8","slug":"definition","fullItemName":"Definition"},{"id":"7d44ea0b-28de-57c5-9ffa-bc6337cf6d42","slug":"prevalence","fullItemName":"Prevalence"},{"id":"85ba124b-cb79-55bf-970f-0ad15fc8f02d","slug":"risk-factors","fullItemName":"Risk factors"},{"id":"297f94a6-ea6d-5e98-8a9b-643eab61b543","slug":"prognosis","fullItemName":"Prognosis"},{"id":"b6f559a3-be4e-53c3-b812-d240ecc27130","slug":"complications","fullItemName":"Complications"}]},{"id":"043a146b-8512-55b9-9f09-5d5cfe0e6149","fullItemName":"Diagnosis","slug":"diagnosis","subChapters":[{"id":"8f1c2235-30d5-59ca-b646-048edf6147eb","slug":"diagnosis","fullItemName":"Diagnosis"},{"id":"9769ec04-f525-59c3-b435-b9d3102c8181","slug":"assessment","fullItemName":"Assessment"},{"id":"06def8c4-72e1-5803-9856-4a5dc3251143","slug":"differential-diagnosis","fullItemName":"Differential diagnosis"}]},{"id":"f6051a87-5d54-56c8-a89a-c0b31d5792cf","fullItemName":"Management","slug":"management","subChapters":[{"id":"ae8728b5-6ae9-581c-8fae-9459f97d2aa6","slug":"management-of-suspected-retinal-detachment","fullItemName":"Scenario: Management of suspected retinal detachment"}]},{"id":"507ad581-89f3-5a8b-b7f6-d3c23c780501","fullItemName":"Supporting evidence","slug":"supporting-evidence","subChapters":[]},{"id":"5425d569-e730-5517-8222-3ac05f1bb17d","fullItemName":"How this topic was developed","slug":"how-this-topic-was-developed","subChapters":[{"id":"b5dddbad-7405-558b-8fa5-2520346a4078","slug":"search-strategy","fullItemName":"Search strategy"},{"id":"9bd58e75-86f4-5e47-8cd9-1e4237228e97","slug":"stakeholder-engagement","fullItemName":"Stakeholder engagement"},{"id":"5feedef8-4110-529a-bdea-a1d7f1d1a6b1","slug":"evidence-exclusion-criteria","fullItemName":"Evidence exclusion criteria"},{"id":"5c697ba5-42f1-504f-9ce2-86117e43f459","slug":"organizational-behavioural-financial-barriers","fullItemName":"Organizational, behavioural and financial barriers"},{"id":"06fa76c3-febb-5a43-b5fe-b23e58638c27","slug":"declarations-of-interest","fullItemName":"Declarations of interest"}]},{"id":"3b42abd9-54a2-5f1c-8dd7-1b5475530ebd","fullItemName":"References","slug":"references","subChapters":[]}]},"parentChapter":{"id":"043a146b-8512-55b9-9f09-5d5cfe0e6149","slug":"diagnosis","fullItemName":"Diagnosis"},"subChapters":[{"id":"dcb75735-e12a-521b-ad83-be17d12386ad","slug":"basis-for-recommendation-ee2","fullItemName":"Basis for recommendation","depth":3,"htmlHeader":"<!-- begin field 887db917-c3e1-41a1-9056-591981629414 --><h3>Basis for recommendation</h3><!-- end field 887db917-c3e1-41a1-9056-591981629414 -->","summary":null,"htmlStringContent":"<!-- begin item ee2c3358-7d3c-4922-8df6-243a940117e2 --><!-- begin field f94ca002-85f1-4943-83ca-b339522f1130 --><p>The recommendations on when to suspect retinal detachment are largely based on expert opinion in the Royal College of Ophthalmologists clinical guidance <em>Management of acute retinal detachment </em>[<a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/retinal-detachment/references/\">Royal College of Ophthalmologists, 2010</a>], the College of Optometrists clinical guidance <em>Examining patients who present with flashes and floaters</em> [<a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/retinal-detachment/references/\">College of Optometrists, 2019</a>], expert opinion in review articles on retinal detachment [<a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/retinal-detachment/references/\">Gariano and Kim, 2004</a>; <a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/retinal-detachment/references/\">Bhagat, 2007</a>], [<a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/retinal-detachment/references/\">D'Amico, 2008</a>; <a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/retinal-detachment/references/\">Kang and Luff, 2008</a>; <a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/retinal-detachment/references/\">Sodhi et al, 2008</a>; <a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/retinal-detachment/references/\">Lumi, 2015</a>], on flashes and floaters [<a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/retinal-detachment/references/\">Khan, 2013</a>; <a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/retinal-detachment/references/\">Sharma, 2015</a>], on loss of vision [<a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/retinal-detachment/references/\">Borooah, 2015</a>], and expert opinion in an ophthalmology textbook [<a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/retinal-detachment/references/\">Yanoff, 2013</a>].</p><ul><li>The information that symptoms can be variable in nature and severity, depending on the location and extent of retinal detachment, is based on expert opinion in review articles [<a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/retinal-detachment/references/\">Gariano and Kim, 2004</a>; <a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/retinal-detachment/references/\">Kang and Luff, 2008</a>].</li><li>The information on the nature of floaters is based on expert opinion in review articles [<a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/retinal-detachment/references/\">Khan, 2013</a>; <a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/retinal-detachment/references/\">Lumi, 2015</a>].</li><li>The information that a diagnosis of retinal detachment can be challenging in children is based on expert opinion in a review article [<a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/retinal-detachment/references/\">Bhagat, 2007</a>].</li></ul><!-- end field f94ca002-85f1-4943-83ca-b339522f1130 --><!-- end item ee2c3358-7d3c-4922-8df6-243a940117e2 -->","subChapters":[]}]}}},"staticQueryHashes":["3666801979"]}